1 6. An update on efforts to support existing home and community treatment services,
2 assertive community treatment services and school-based treatment services programs;
3 7. An update on the development of the level of care provided by a psychiatric
4 residential treatment facility for children in this State;
5 8. An update on the federal certified community behavioral health clinic Medicaid
6 demonstration program;
7 9. An update on the development of crisis receiving centers for children; and
8 10. An update on the services that are needed and unavailable, causing children to
9 remain in hospital emergency departments and inpatient settings awaiting behavioral health
10 services after they are cleared for discharge.'
11 Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
12 takes effect when approved.'
13 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
14 number to read consecutively.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This amendment makes several changes to the bill.
17 1. It removes from the bill the sections requiring an out-of-state and emergency
18 department cost analysis, changes to the aftercare services payment model and one-time
19 funding to stabilize children's residential care facilities in danger of closing.
20 2. It adds requirements to the annual report on children's behavioral health services
21 from the Department of Health and Human Services related to children in hospital
22 emergency departments after they are cleared for discharge, out-of-state residential services
23 and the cost of those services, lengths of stays in residential treatment facilities and denials
24 of services.
25 3. It requires the department to engage in outreach to providers of children's residential
26 services, inpatient psychiatric services and community-based services to prevent closures
27 and encourage the reopening of beds.
28 4. It requires the department to provide a report to the Joint Standing Committee on
29 Health and Human Services, no later than December 3, 2025, with data and policy efforts
30 related to children's behavioral health services.
31 5. It adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause.
